## Open a workshop

Pick a branch name. Two commands:

```bash
cd {{ _repo_path }}
git worktree add workshops/<branch> -b <branch> main
cd workshops/<branch>
```

Claude users: `claude --worktree <branch>` from the CLI, or ask Claude to call `EnterWorktree` from inside a session. Both routes go through `.claude/hooks/worktree-create`.

## Who merges what

`workshops/main/` is the maintainer's workshop. Open an MR against `main`; the maintainer reviews and merges from there. Don't push to `main` from your own workshop — the bare repo's hooks will reject it.

See [Worktree Workshops 🛠️](https://cute-devops.patterns.how/patterns/approaches/worktree-workshops) for the full pattern.

